# Expo official skills (`expo/skills`)

This project should use the Expo team’s official agent skills for building, deploying, and debugging Expo apps.

**Source:** [https://github.com/expo/skills](https://github.com/expo/skills)

## Install in Cursor (Remote Rule)

1. Open **Cursor Settings** (macOS: Cmd+Shift+J, Windows/Linux: Ctrl+Shift+J).
2. Go to **Rules & Command** → **Project Rules** → **Add Rule** → **Remote Rule (GitHub)**.
3. Enter: `https://github.com/expo/skills.git`

Skills are picked up by context; they do not show under `/` (that menu is for custom commands in `.cursor/commands/`, not skills).

**Check:** Ask something Expo-specific (e.g. Expo Router UI, API calls in Expo, App Store deployment). Answers should lean on the installed skills when they match.

## Optional: copy skills locally (any agent)

```bash
bunx skills add expo/skills
```

You must upgrade those copies manually when the upstream repo changes.

## Agent behavior

When the user’s task involves Expo (Router, native APIs, EAS, debugging, UI patterns, data fetching in Expo, etc.), prefer guidance that aligns with the **expo/skills** content when it is available in context. Do not contradict those skills without a project-specific reason documented in this repo’s other rules (e.g. `expo.mdc`, `project.mdc`).
